# Customization

Tailwind CSS is designed to be highly customizable. You can extend or override the default configuration to match your project's design system perfectly. The main configuration file is `tailwind.config.js`.

---

## 1. Basic Configuration File

When you run `npx tailwindcss init`, it creates a basic configuration file:

```javascript
/** @type {import('tailwindcss').Config} */
module.exports = {
  content: [
    "./src/**/*.{html,js,jsx,ts,tsx}",
  ],
  theme: {
    extend: {},
  },
  plugins: [],
}
```

### Extended Configuration Example:
```javascript
/** @type {import('tail

windcss').Config} */
module.exports = {
  content: [
    "./src/**/*.{html,js,jsx,ts,tsx}",
    "./public/index.html",
  ],
  darkMode: 'class', // or 'media'
  theme: {
    extend: {
      colors: {
        brand: {
          primary: '#1E40AF',
          secondary: '#DC2626',
        }
      },
      fontFamily: {
        sans: ['Inter', 'system-ui', 'sans-serif'],
      },
    },
  },
  plugins: [
    require('@tailwindcss/forms'),
    require('@tailwindcss/typography'),
  ],
}
```

---

## 2. Color Customization

### Extending Colors (Recommended)
```javascript
module.exports = {
  theme:

{
    extend: {
      colors: {
        // Add new colors
        brand: {
          50: '#f0f9ff',
          100: '#e0f2fe',
          200: '#bae6fd',
          300: '#7dd3fc',
          400: '#38bdf8',
          500: '#0ea5e9',
          600: '#0284c7',
          700: '#0369a1',
          800: '#075985',
          900: '#0c4a6e',
          950: '#082f49',
        },
        // Single custom color
        'custom-orange': '#FF6B35',
        // Using CSS variables
        'primary': 'var(--color-primary)',
        'secondary': 'var(--color-secondary)',
      },
    },
  },
}
```

### Overridin

g Colors (Replace Defaults)
```javascript
module.exports = {
  theme: {
    colors: {
      // Completely replace the default color palette
      transparent: 'transparent',
      current: 'currentColor',
      black: '#000',
      white: '#fff',
      gray: {
        50: '#f9fafb',
        100: '#f3f4f6',
        // ... custom gray shades
      },
      // Your custom colors
      primary: {
        500: '#3B82F6',
        600: '#2563EB',
      },
    },
  },
}
```

**Usage:**
```html
<div class="bg-brand-500 text-white p-4">Brand Color</div>
<button class="bg-custom-orange text-white px-4 py

-2">Custom Orange</button>
```

