## 10. Using CSS Variables

### Configuring with CSS Variables
```javascript
// tailwind.config.js
module.exports = {
  theme: {
    extend: {
      colors: {
        primary: 'var(--color-primary)',
        secondary: 'var(--color-secondary)',
        accent: 'var(--color-accent)',
      },
      spacing: {
        'header': 'var(--header-height)',
        'sidebar': 'var(--sidebar-width)',
      },
    },
  },
}
```

### CSS File with Variables
```css
/* styles.css */
:root {
  --color-primary:

 #3B82F6;
  --color-secondary: #10B981;
  --color-accent: #8B5CF6;
  --header-height: 64px;
  --sidebar-width: 280px;
}

.dark {
  --color-primary: #60A5FA;
  --color-secondary: #34D399;
  --color-accent: #A78BFA;
}
```

**Usage:**
```html
<div class="bg-primary text-white p-4">Primary color</div>
<header class="h-header">Header with custom height</header>
```

